                                <div class="timeline-arrow"></div>
                                <h2 class="h3 mb-0">Simulation of Bile Action</h2>
                                <ul class="fs-5 mt-2 font-weight-light">
                                    <li class="my-3 list-group-item">Explain the role of bile in digestion. Is it
                                        involved
                                        in chemical or mechanical digestion?
                                        <ul class="fs-6 my-2 font-weight-light">
                                            <li>Bile is essential for fat digestion since it is generated by the liver
                                                and
                                                stored in the gallbladder. Bile works as a mechanical facilitator in the
                                                small intestine by emulsifying big fat globules into smaller droplets,
                                                improving the surface area to volume ratio. This mechanical process
                                                improves
                                                the efficiency of lipases, which are enzymes that break down lipids into
                                                fatty acids and glycerol during chemical digestion. Bile's
                                                emulsification
                                                role, in essence, optimizes both mechanical and chemical elements of fat
                                                digestion.</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
